Lower numbers are always safer, but at some point, the value is personally not worth it. A child will grab a quarter off the ground and be excited, while most adults may see that same quarter and deem it not even worth bending down to grab it. Value is a logarithmic scale, and it explains why things such as valet parking is common amount certain income levels, because $20 here or there has less value to them than time and convince if their basal wealth is high enough. The concern with the human condition is that not only does perception of time and experience change as we age, but also the perception of value; therefore how can a population of various ages and perceptions live together cohesively and agree on the same goals?
